<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="181" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 874.00/16: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                Peace</gloss> to the Consul General at Saloniki</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Horton</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-27">December 27,
                                1918</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>3. Your 18th to Embassy Paris transmitting number 5 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>] from Sofia.<note n="13" xml:id="d181fn13">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_250">p. 250</ref>.</note> Kindly inform
                        Mr. Wilson that President desires an expression of his thanks conveyed to
                        Bulgarian Prime Minister for his congratulations, and say to Mr. Wilson that
                        other matter mentioned in his telegram must of necessity in present
                        circumstances await action of French Government on the request addressed to
                        it.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>